### makeAllowedFCmpRegion() {#a84ec432d02febd1b518e9453b1a0eba9}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>ConstantFPRange ConstantFPRange::makeAllowedFCmpRegion (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/cmpinst/#a2be3583dac92a031fa1458d4d992c78b">FCmpInst::Predicate</a> Pred, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantfprange">ConstantFPRange</a> &amp; Other)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Produce the smallest range such that all values that may satisfy the given predicate with any value contained within Other is contained in the returned range.

Formally, this returns a superset of &#39;union over all y in Other . &#123; x : fcmp op x y is true &#125;&#39;. If the exact answer is not representable as a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantfprange">ConstantFPRange</a>, the return value will be a proper superset of the above.

Example: Pred = ole and Other = float &#91;2, 5&#93; returns Result = &#91;-inf, 5&#93;

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/constantfprange-h/#l00107">107</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/constantfprange-h">ConstantFPRange.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/constantfprange-cpp/#l00164">164</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/ir/constantfprange-cpp">ConstantFPRange.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<MemberDefinition

### makeSatisfyingFCmpRegion() {#a4c7a26e0bf4a7880f0ba8c3aa2d74a89}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>ConstantFPRange ConstantFPRange::makeSatisfyingFCmpRegion (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/cmpinst/#a2be3583dac92a031fa1458d4d992c78b">FCmpInst::Predicate</a> Pred, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantfprange">ConstantFPRange</a> &amp; Other)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Produce the largest range such that all values in the returned range satisfy the given predicate with all values contained within Other.

Formally, this returns a subset of &#39;intersection over all y in Other . &#123; x : fcmp op x y is true &#125;&#39;. If the exact answer is not representable as a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/constantfprange">ConstantFPRange</a>, the return value will be a proper subset of the above.

Example: Pred = ole and Other = float &#91;2, 5&#93; returns &#91;-inf, 2&#93;
